Here's a structured overview of Kubernetes (K8s) topics — ideal for learning from scratch, preparing for certifications like CKA (Certified Kubernetes Administrator), or mastering container orchestration in production environments.

🧱 1. Kubernetes Basics
What is Kubernetes?

Kubernetes vs Docker

Architecture Overview:

Master Components: API Server, Scheduler, Controller Manager, etcd

Node Components: kubelet, kube-proxy, container runtime

Cluster setup: Minikube, kubeadm, kind, managed (EKS, GKE, AKS)

📦 2. Core Concepts
Pods (basic deployable unit)

ReplicaSets (ensures a specified number of pod replicas)

Deployments (manages ReplicaSets)

Namespaces (virtual clusters within a physical cluster)

Labels & Selectors (used for grouping)

Annotations (metadata)

🏗️ 3. Workload Management
DaemonSets (one pod per node)

StatefulSets (for stateful apps like databases)

Jobs and CronJobs (batch/recurring tasks)

Horizontal Pod Autoscaler (HPA)

Init Containers and Sidecars

📡 4. Networking
Kubernetes Networking Model

ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer Services

DNS in Kubernetes

Ingress and Ingress Controllers

Network Policies (security rules for traffic)

📁 5. Storage
Volumes (emptyDir, hostPath, configMap, secret, etc.)

Persistent Volumes (PV)

Persistent Volume Claims (PVC)

StorageClasses

Dynamic provisioning

🔐 6. Security & Access Control
RBAC (Role-Based Access Control)

Service Accounts

Network Policies

Pod Security Standards (Baseline, Restricted)

Secrets and ConfigMaps (for injecting configs/secrets into pods)

🛠️ 7. Configuration & Management
kubectl CLI basics

YAML manifests: Structure and writing

Helm (package manager for Kubernetes)

Kustomize (built-in tool for customizing manifests)

📈 8. Monitoring & Logging
Liveness & Readiness Probes

Prometheus + Grafana (metrics)

ELK / EFK Stack (logging)

Kubernetes Events

Resource Limits & Requests

🔄 9. Updates & Maintenance
Rolling updates

Rollbacks

Taints & Tolerations (for controlling pod placement)

Draining & cordoning nodes

☁️ 10. Cloud & CI/CD Integration
Kubernetes on AWS (EKS), Azure (AKS), GCP (GKE)

GitOps (ArgoCD, FluxCD)

Integrating with Jenkins, GitHub Actions, etc.

Custom Resource Definitions (CRDs) & Operators

📜 11. Advanced Topics
Custom Controllers

API Aggregation Layer

Admission Controllers

Webhooks

Multi-cluster management

Service Mesh (Istio, Linkerd)


